  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pelvic fracture surgery are very high thrombotic risk surgery with about 10% to 50% venous
      thrombo embolic complications and 0.5% to 10% of pulmonary embolism. The ST JOSEPH's Hospital
      have almost 60 cases per year . Following a fatal pulmonary embolism per operatory the team
      has set up a venous exploratory protocol before surgery.

      This protocol includes a venous doppler ultrasound of lower limbs associated to a abdo pelvic
      scanner in the 48hours before surgery.

      The aim is to evaluate this new protocol efficacy on prevention of thrombo embolic
      complications in pelvic fracture surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
